A simple interpreter for the pure fragment of Verse.
It desugars the source Verse expression into Core
and can run it using
  :eval      uses the rules, but with various shortcuts to make
             it more efficient
  :rewrite   uses exactly the POPL rules and explores all possible
             execution paths to make sure they all agree

Installing necessary Haskell stuff:
  Get ghcup:
    see https://www.haskell.org/ghcup/
  Install ghc:
    ghcup install ghc
  Install cabal:
    ghcup install cabal
  Install packages:
    cabal v1-install megaparsec
    cabal v1-install QuickCheck

Build:
  make

Run:  (The UI is a bit sucky.)
  ./verse

Run tests:
  ./tests
